      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Wine Quality Prediction (Classification) — Red Wine\n",
        "\n",
        "## Objective\n",
        "Predict wine quality category using classification models based on physicochemical properties.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Design Decisions (Instructor-aligned)\n",
        "- **Regroup labels**: Low (≤5), Medium (=6), High (≥7).\n",
        "- **Separate analysis**: Red and white wines are analysed separately due to different chemical distributions.\n",
        "- **≥3 models**: GaussianNB, Logistic Regression, Random Forest.\n",
        "- **Metrics based on problem understanding**:\n",
        "  - The regrouped classes are imbalanced, so **macro-F1** is used as the primary metric.\n",
        "  - Accuracy is reported as a secondary reference.\n",
        "- **Improvements implemented in coding**:\n",
        "  - Data exploration (EDA) + feature analysis\n",
        "  - Missing/duplicate checks (duplicates removed if any)\n",
        "  - Correlation analysis\n",
        "  - Outlier-robust scaling (RobustScaler)\n",
        "  - Class weighting (imbalance handling)\n",
        "  - Stratified 5-fold cross-validation (mean ± std)\n",
        "  - GridSearchCV tuning (macro-F1 objective)\n",
        "  - Overfitting analysis (train vs test; CV vs test)\n",
        "  - Deeper error analysis (normalized confusion matrix + top confusions)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "feR4oXDB5VeC"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "IVXiL45uKndR"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, StratifiedKFold, cross_validate, GridSearchCV\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import RobustScaler\n",
        "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
        "    classification_report,\n",
        "    confusion_matrix,\n",
        "    ConfusionMatrixDisplay,\n",
        "    f1_score,\n",
        "    accuracy_score\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB\n",
        "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier"
      ]
    },
